To split a new dataset, download the appropriate year and annotations file:
   
   http://cocodataset.org/#download

From the project root, make the test and training directories for the resulting split:
   
   mkdir -p ./data/test
   mkdir -p ./data/train

Run the script:

    python3 split_coco.py --from-image-path <images_directory> --annotations <annotations_file.json> --to-train-path ./data/train/ --to-test-path ./data/test/ --split-percent .8

You can adjust the split percentage. It must in the range (0, 1).
      
